    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>PAROLE LAWSUIT</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By KAREN DeMASTERS</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Demasters, Karen</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Three inmates at Riverfront State Prison in New Jersey file suit on behalf of about 300 to 1,000 prisoners alleging prisoners are being denied timely parole hearings (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A lawsuit filed last week in United States District Court in Camden says prisoners are being denied timely parole hearings. The suit was filed by three inmates at Riverfront State Prison on behalf of what is estimated at 300 to 1,000 prisoners whose parole dates have gone by, some as long as 15 months ago, without the state parole board holding a hearing.</p>
        <p>KAREN DeMASTERS</p>
      </block>
